# Zero-build plugin: control BOTH the WordPress.org SVN trunk contents and the GitHub-generated zip
# from one place. The 10up deploy action honors these `export-ignore` rules (no build step), and
# `git archive` applies them too, so the GitHub Release zip == what ships to WP.org.
#
# Everything NOT listed here is plugin source and DOES ship: LICENSE, readme.txt, rigpolice-embed.php,
# render.php, block.json, index.js, index.asset.php, editor.css.
#
# .wordpress-org is export-ignored from trunk on purpose — the action copies it to the SVN `assets/`
# dir (banners/icons/screenshots), so shipping it in trunk too would duplicate it.

/.git                   export-ignore
/.github                export-ignore
/.gitattributes         export-ignore
/.gitignore             export-ignore
/.distignore            export-ignore
/.wordpress-org         export-ignore
/.wp-env                export-ignore
/.wp-env.json           export-ignore
/.wp-env.override.json  export-ignore
/README.md              export-ignore
